item.title: The Tauminator (Space Communist)
item.description:
The Tauminator has arrived! Combining the absolute cutting edge technology from the Space Communists and the most powerful armor of the humans, one of the most powerful warriors in the galaxy was created. Piloted by a genetically enhanced elite veteran, this Space Communist has little foes that can match its power!

This is a kitbash inspired by a post I saw on reddit, with a little bit of my spin on it. I have included a blender file along with it, for easier remixing if wanted. The whole model that is included, I just used for the render, warning it is not properly merged.

Its been a while since my last upload, I know. Ended up helping a buddy with his business, which lead me to basically working 2 full time jobs. Leaving me with a lot less time to model. That is pretty much over with now, so expect some more releases in the future.

As Always if you like the model and want to see more please like and comment.

item.title: Beach Walker
item.description:
This is a special crutch cap that can be put on and taken off a crutch or walking stick. The cap has a bigger surface so the user of these caps can walk on soft terrain.The spacers have to be fixed with the following:

  • DIN 934 nuts M3
  • DIN 7991 bolts M3x8mm

The beach walker itself has a tube on the outside and this is used to fix the beach walker to the spacers. To fix the beach walker you need a hose clamp that has an inner diameter of 55 mm.

This thing is invented for people with walking disabilities or those who don't have the strength to walk as much anymore to be able to walk on soft terrains like beaches or trails.

If you want to print this and make it functional then it is recommended you print this with nylon (PA 12) and use an SLS printer. FDM printing can be used but it won't be as strong as SLS printing.

item.title: (WIP) Samsung Galaxy S8 g950 case
item.description:
This is a work in progress, the case could not fit on your phone. This test case was made for the regular Samsung Galaxy S8; for the S8+ see this; and for the S8 Active see this. For different reasons, I have trouble to test some of the phone cases I have designed. So that, I left the cases uploaded; in case anyone wants to help me testing them. I would really appreciate any feedback on the models. I will need:
  • Photos of the phone with the case printed.
  • The material you used, that could be PLA, ABS, PETG, HIPS or Nylon, but not flexible filaments.
  • The exact model of your phone. In this case can be G950F, G950FD, G950U, G950A, G950P, G950T, G950V, G950R4, G950W, G950S, G950K, G950L or G9500.
  • A description of how it fits.
Once I have a tested ok model I will publish the final versions for rigid and flexible materials, of course crediting my testers.
For other phone cases check this.

  • GSMArena

item.title: Sunlu Filadryer S1 4010 Fan mount (non-flex)
item.description:
I remixed this to be printable in any non-flex material. The fan just slides in from the top. I removed the right sidewall to allow for a small stepdown converter (I run the stock Ender 3 part cooling fan at 12V, which is basically completely unhearable) to be stuck to it with doublesided tape.
I found that there are actually 2 models of this fan, one which has thinner walls around the screws and one that has full thickness. The included STLs will fit one type each.
Print upright without supports.

item.title: Robbes
item.description:
This is an example design for my OpenScad course.

I was inspired by https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:1267209/files, but only roughly took the idea of the structure, the Thing is heavily modified.

In my course, I want to arouse interest in design and 3D printing in young people. I will also explain 3D print-optimized design.

The example was designed accordingly and can be printed without supports. The most important possibilities of the software are shown in the modular OpenScad files.

As an LED I have provided a multiple color flashing LED, it has built-in electronics and is operated with 3V, suitable for the CR2032 battery.

Dies ist eine Beispielkonstruktion für meinen OpenScad Kurs.

Ich war inspiriert von https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:1267209/files, habe aber nur die Idee des Aufbaus grob übernommen, das Thing ist stark abgewandelt.

In meinem Kurs möchte ich bei Jugendlichen das Interesse am Konstruktieren und 3D-Drucken wecken. Ich werde auch 3D-druckoptimiertes Konstruieren erläutern.

Das Beispiel wurde dazu entsprechend gestaltet und ist ohne Supports druckbar. In den modular gestalteten OpenScad Files werden die wichtigsten Möglichkeiten der Software gezeigt.

Als LED habe ich eine Mehrfach-Farb-Blink LED vorgesehen, sie hat eine eingebaute Elektronik und wird mit 3V betrieben, passend zur Batterie CR2032.

item.title: SUNLU 3D Filament Dryer Box S1 Guide
item.description:
I Made this for the Sunlu single filament dryer box on amazon:

https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B08C9RZPMN

I did this because sometimes the filament would un-spool a little and contact the heater element that lines the bottom of the box. This can distort it enough when hot to risk kinking.

I kept the tolerance pretty tight so it will actually hold the box closed. Use a knife to shave it down a little to your preference.
item.author: aesalazar

item.title: Single Stage and QoL Remix
item.description:
- The images used are of my prototype blaster printed in odds and ends of filament at lower quality settings -

I started to put together a solenoid powered Gryphon but came across some small issues with the original files, I had heads of screws interfering with printed pieces or holes not large enough for screw heads to fit. So I modified the files I needed to make my screws fit better, I also tweaked the grips to cover some hardware that was now visible with the solenoid design too.

I also modified a standard Talon cage (grip version) with the necessary adjustments to allow the solenoid pusher to work, this then allows any front end to be used with the solenoid grip, be it single stage or even a carbine front. Due to changes in the height of the top solenoid cover, I also have a shortened top Picatinny rail for use with a single-stage blaster.

As my blaster was going to have the battery under the grip I modified the grip to allow the wires to come out of the bottom, added a little more inside for wires as well as a proper catch position for the end of the trigger spring. To cover the hole in the bottom for people who don't want their battery under the grip I have included a sling mount to attach to cover the hole.

Finally, I have also created a nerf compatible stock point, this will allow the attachment of any nerf compatible stock, I have made the central core removable so you can use a battery stock with the blaster.

item.title: Gamepad Thumb Style Stick-ends for Jumper T-lite
item.description:
These are PS4 inspired stick ends for the Jumper T-Lite for people who like to fly with their thumbs. They were designed with the following features in mind:

  1. Lowest possible profile: only 1mm higher than the end of the gimbal's shaft
  2. Largest pad that clears the Jumper's body at full corner deflection
  3. Rounded edge of the pad so as you transition from having your thumb on the pad to using the edge (when pushing forward) you have maximum contact for grip
  4. Thumb sized pad with a ridge for maximum grip and control in the center
